1
00:00:05,183 --> 00:00:06,898
It's a very broad subject,

2
00:00:06,898 --> 00:00:09,503
'what is the happiness in Krishna consciousness?'

3
00:00:09,825 --> 00:00:12,610

4
00:00:12,811 --> 00:00:15,673
As Kaviraj Goswami tells us,

5
00:00:15,843 --> 00:00:21,000
bāhye viṣa-jvālā haya,bhitare ānanda-maya,

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,994
kṛṣṇa-premāra adbhuta charita

7
00:00:24,994 --> 00:00:29,819
the 'adbhuta charita', wonderful, wonderfully

8
00:00:29,819 --> 00:00:37,020
astonishing characteristic of Krishna prema,

9
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,097
the highest type of Krishna consciousness,

10
00:00:40,097 --> 00:00:45,861
is that, although externally one appears to be suffering,

11
00:00:45,861 --> 00:00:49,140
internally, they're relishing some

12
00:00:49,140 --> 00:00:53,486
extraordinary type of sweetness.

13
00:00:53,486 --> 00:00:56,946
So we kinda have a stereotype

14
00:00:56,946 --> 00:01:01,100
about what is happiness in Krishna consciousness.

15
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:08,986
In the Brhad Bhagavatamrtam of Sanatan Goswami,

16
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:13,822
when he's concluding, perhaps the first section,

17
00:01:13,822 --> 00:01:19,617
he's saying, "The real rasik devotees of the Lord,

18
00:01:19,617 --> 00:01:23,402
they alone understand the joy

19
00:01:23,402 --> 00:01:28,986
and the superiority of Viraha,

20
00:01:28,986 --> 00:01:33,420
of separation. That, if Krishna consciousness

21
00:01:33,420 --> 00:01:39,221
is about depth of love,

22
00:01:39,221 --> 00:01:43,069
'hladini shakti', the sār of Hladini

23
00:01:43,069 --> 00:01:46,382
is prema, bhava, the sār of that -

24
00:01:46,382 --> 00:01:50,021
the cream of that - bhava, maha bhava,

25
00:01:50,021 --> 00:01:51,700
ultimately.

26
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:54,057
Maha bhava means in this sense,

27
00:01:54,057 --> 00:01:55,500
the greatest heart,

28
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:58,821
who possesses the greatest heart,

29
00:01:58,821 --> 00:02:02,580
full of Krishna consciousness to the greatest degree,

30
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:04,986
the greatest depth of heart?

31
00:02:04,986 --> 00:02:07,742
Srimati Radharani,

32
00:02:07,742 --> 00:02:09,582
'maha bhav swarupani, Radha thakurani'

33
00:02:09,582 --> 00:02:14,260
Hladini shakti, personified.

34
00:02:14,260 --> 00:02:18,662
We're told that, so, if this is about

35
00:02:18,662 --> 00:02:21,070
achieving the greatest depths of heart

36
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:25,022
and magnitude of heart, intensity,

37
00:02:25,022 --> 00:02:26,901
Guru Maharaj revealed - and,

38
00:02:26,901 --> 00:02:29,180
we're back in Golden Volcano,

39
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:31,263
divine lava -

40
00:02:31,263 --> 00:02:34,260
that in separation, a greater depth

41
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:37,340
and magnitude and intensity of heart

42
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:40,460
is achieved than in union.

43
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:45,376
So when Srila Gurudev

44
00:02:45,376 --> 00:02:48,902
was dealing with this question once,

45
00:02:48,902 --> 00:02:52,989
he said with some - almost disgust,

46
00:02:52,989 --> 00:02:57,621
that someone was trying to put forth the idea

47
00:02:57,621 --> 00:03:03,136
that union was higher than separation,

48
00:03:03,136 --> 00:03:09,460
and Gurudev said, 'Even the animals know about union.'

49
00:03:09,460 --> 00:03:13,985
and he said, 'Goats, they understand something about union.'

50
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:20,340
He said, 'But who understands the peculiar joy of separation?

51
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:24,823
Not the animals, certainly.'

52
00:03:24,823 --> 00:03:30,351
Guru Maharaj liked to quote Shelley,

53
00:03:30,536 --> 00:03:33,543
saying "Our sweetest tales

54
00:03:33,543 --> 00:03:37,580
are those full of the saddest thoughts."

55
00:03:37,580 --> 00:03:41,260
He said, what is the Krishna prema?

56
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:43,540
The real joy, happiness, in Krishna consciouness

57
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:47,152
appears like you've been bitten,

58
00:03:47,152 --> 00:03:50,420
poisoned by a cobra, and you're haemorrhaging.

59
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:57,262
Well, bathing in a shower of nectar at the same time.

60
00:03:57,262 --> 00:03:59,359
If you can hold these two things,

61
00:03:59,359 --> 00:04:01,820
it's almost counter-intuitive

62
00:04:01,820 --> 00:04:09,649
or, what's the sanskrit expression..

63
00:04:09,649 --> 00:04:13,703
regarding two opposites being held

64
00:04:13,703 --> 00:04:18,240
in the mind at the same time?

65
00:04:18,363 --> 00:04:22,570
I can't remember the phrase now,

66
00:04:22,570 --> 00:04:24,941
but, these two peculiar

67
00:04:24,941 --> 00:04:29,068
polar opposites, in a sense, simultaneously,

68
00:04:29,068 --> 00:04:31,622
saying, 'that's the actual position

69
00:04:31,622 --> 00:04:34,486
of the higher devotees.'

70
00:04:34,486 --> 00:04:38,022
But as indicated in the Bhagavad Gita

71
00:04:38,022 --> 00:04:39,940
by Srila Guru Maharaj,

72
00:04:43,893 --> 00:04:46,817
when the devotees are discussing

73
00:04:46,817 --> 00:04:52,416
these pastimes, the wide variety of pastimes,

74
00:04:52,416 --> 00:04:57,068
it's as if they're feasting,

75
00:04:57,068 --> 00:05:00,541
that's 'tushanti', like when we have a big feast

76
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,020
and there's one tasteful thing after another,

77
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:03,702
and you're tasting this, and,

78
00:05:03,702 --> 00:05:05,262
the next thing is more tasteful than that,

79
00:05:05,262 --> 00:05:06,568
another tasteful thing, another tasteful thing,

80
00:05:06,568 --> 00:05:11,420
and as much as you feel nourished,

81
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:19,068
and acquiring strength and vitality from that,

82
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:23,016
that's what the devotees get,

83
00:05:23,016 --> 00:05:25,622
hearing, that's their pleasure,

84
00:05:25,622 --> 00:05:29,378
hearing and chanting about Krishna.

85
00:05:29,378 --> 00:05:32,020
But, that said, the sweetest songs

86
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:34,975
are those that tell the saddest tales.

87
00:05:34,975 --> 00:05:38,975
Hare Krishna.

